A Note to the Harvest<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
To the Violent Harvest:<br>
<br>
Greetings. My name is Kassy Lightborn, though you may have heard me called Kassy Na'Verdis, as this is what Nospiratus has seen fit to call me. Kassy who knows no truth. This is far from accurate.<br>
<br>
Never before did I look for trouble with the Harvest, yet trouble, it would seem, has found me. More and more often as I walk through the area surrounding my home do I see your young brethren and I cannot help but wonder at the increasing activity around my beloved Qeynos. <br>
<br>
I am not violent by nature, and I hold within my heart no Hate for the individual members of the Harvest, for in my present state I fear what Hate might lead me to. I do not judge on the color of one's skin or the profession they choose to follow as I myself ask not to be judged by such. The Harvest, itself, however, is another matter. My understanding, and do correct me if I am mistaken, is that you seek to bring about dread Innoruuk's rule of Norrath. You are mad to desire such a thing! Do not mistake my kindness or Lightborn ways for weakness. Though I would rather talk over mugs of wine than do battle, I will fight to protect myself, my friends, and my home. I will not be hurt by Innoruuk again, nor will I allow my friends to be.<br>
<br>
Hear me, Harvest, keep to your dark forest, your deep city. Do not seek to extend the range of that darkness for the world cannot survive without the life-giving light and without Norrath you yourselves will surely perish.<br>
<br>
You call me Kassy Na'Verdis, yet I know much. I have felt the very touch of your Dark Innoruuk and it is not something I would wish upon my most despised enemy. I will not allow you to bring his touch, his Hate, to others if it is at all within my power.<br>
<br>
Be well then, Harvest. I pray you come to see the truth of the Light that we might meet on friendly terms. It is truly a day I hope to see and, Tunare willing, one day I shall.<br>
<br>
Kassy Lightborn<br>
Daughter of Tunare <br>
