Numadar reflects back upon the first time he meet this Kassy that he is reading about now. Standing in the entrance of the East Commons tunnel awaiting a trader whom he had a business deal arranged with, he heard a soft spoken insult masked by a smile whisper it's way into his ear. &quot;I just can't escape all of you VIOLENT HARVEST. You are everywhere.&quot; was the way Kassy introduced herself to me. I turned slightly to direct my eyes upon a beautiful Teir'dal girl who wore the sign of Tunare around her neck. I thought to myself, &quot;Now isn't this the most peculiar thing I have seen in a long time.&quot; Surveying this young darkelf girl I gathered that she was an enchantress by trade. Never had I seen someone with such a lost look in their eyes before than what I saw before me now. &quot;Do I know you?&quot; I asked. &quot;No you do not and that is how I wish it to be evil one. I would not wish to know the dark and misguided followers of Innoruuk who have nothing but Hate in their hearts such as you.&quot; was her response. With my hand extended I took a step toward her to introduce myself, &quot;Hello I am Numadar.&quot; She shrank back against the wall of the tunnel and said, &quot;My name is Kassy Lightborn, but your mad prophet calls by another.&quot; Laughter erupted from my lungs so loud that all trading ceased for a moment to see what was so funny. Even a dueling set of warriors took notice for a second to look at me. The barbarion swiftly took the humans head off for paying attention a little too long. How hilarious is this? A Teir'dal girl by the name of Lightborn. Oh what a misguided soul this must be. And the name that the prophet had given her, I still laugh to myself everytime I think about it. At this moment Kassy began chanting and Invoked an Illusion upon herself of the woodelf form. Her eyes held no Illusion though. In them I could see the lost soul inside of her that was reaching out for her identity that she so greatly missed in her life. The denial of who she was. Standing there looking like a fare skinned druid girl her Teir'Dal eyes betrayed her true self to me. &quot;Why do you hide yourself young Teir'dal girl? Why do you wish to be a &quot;Faker&quot; as I like to call it?&quot; Kassy shouted at me, &quot;I'm not a Teir'dal!&quot; At that moment a gnome walked up to her and said, &quot;Kind druid, might you cast the spirit of the wolf on me for a long trip I am about to embark upon?&quot; Kassy dropped the Illusion immediatly and told the small one he was mistaken about her trade. He walked away mumbling about damn enchanters or something like that. So this was my first encounter with the young lost soul that sends messages to us about how wrong we are. We spoke for several hours after this about the merits of each others beliefs. All the details of our conversation would require a month to put into writing, but I did learn some very important things about her that night that do need to be said. Kassy was gifted by Innoruuk early in her life, sculpting her into the darkelf woman that she is now. Saving her from a life of false hopes as the woodelf that she would have been. Kassy mistakes this as a curse upon her life though. She fights so hard to deny her true self that she sought out the Knights Templar to make her feel that she truely is a Lightborn. The Knights toyed with her and gave false promises and hopes that she would one day be one of them. In the end they crushed her and sent her away, stating to her that she should perish with her Teir'dal bretheran in Hate. What an evil situation. Hated by the ones she wanted to be, and hating the ones who would welcome her with open arms. But Kassy can't accept what she is doing now. I see her cries of help to us everytime she screams words of hate at us. She doesn't seek out the harvest and the Teir'dal brothers because she wants us to fail. She seeks us out because we are the only ones that will ever truely accept her into the family. Kassy is just lost and in need of guidance. She is a lost soul that is wondering Norrath looking for an identity. I say seek her out and show her the pride of being a Teir'dal. She can mask herself in Illusions but the blood that flows through her is that of our own blood. Kassy needs to understand what a GIFT she has been given and relish in it.<br>
